tDaemonOptions(): Option[] {\n  return [\n    new Option('-p, --port <number>', 'TCP port'),\n    new Option('--host <address>', 'Host address'),\n    new Option('--listen <transport>', 'Transport').choices(DAEMON_LISTEN_MODE_VALUES).default(DaemonListenMode.WebSocket),\n    // ...\n  ];\n}\n```\n\n`index.ts` stays minimal вҖ” imports only lightweight option files, applies them to stubs:\n\n```ts\nimport { getDaemonOptions } from '@/commands/daemon/options';\n\nconst daemonCmd = program.command('daemon').description('Run the Factory daemon server');\nfor (const opt of getDaemonOptions()) daemonCmd.addOption(opt);\ndaemonCmd.action(async () => { await import('@/entrypoints/daemon'); });\n```\n\nFor exec: options remain in `commands/exec.ts` (too many, some dynamic). The index.ts stub stays option-free.\n\n### Phase 3b: Trim `index.ts` \n\nRemove all option definitions that now live in per-command option files. The only options remaining on the root `program` are the truly global ones: `--settings`, `--append-system-prompt`, `--append-system-prompt-file`, `-r/--resume`, `--fork`, `--cwd`, `-w/--worktree`, `--worktree-dir` (these are TUI-only and consumed by `entrypoints/tui.ts`).\n\n---\n\n## Updated `index.ts` dispatch (after all phases)\n\n```ts\nimport { Command, Option } from 'commander';\nimport { getDaemonOptions } from '@/commands/daemon/options';\n\nconst program = new Command();\nprogram.name('droid').version(process.env.CLI_VERSION || 'unknown', '-v, --version');\n// Global TUI options (only needed for routing correctness)\nprogram.addOption(new Option('--settings <path>', '...'));\nprogram.addOption(new Option('-r, --resume [sessionId]', '...'));\n// ... other global opts\n\n// CLI subcommands вҖ” each with own entrypoint\nconst daemonCmd = program.command('daemon').description('...');\nfor (const opt of getDaemonOptions()) daemonCmd.addOption(opt);\ndaemonCmd.action(async () => { await import('@/entrypoints/daemon'); });\n\nprogram.command('search').alias(