            "plan": "## Prerequisite: Upgrade Commander\n\nUpgrade `commander` from `^11.0.0` (installed: 10.0.1) to `^14.0.3` in both `apps/cli` and `apps/scripts`.\n\n**Breaking changes to address:**\n- v13: excess arguments error by default вҶ’ add `.allowExcessArguments()` on the TUI default command (it uses `[prompt...]`)\n- v12: throws on duplicate option flags/command names вҶ’ shouldn't affect us since commands are distinct\n- No multi-char short flags exist in codebase вң“\n\n**New features to leverage:**\n- **Help groups** (v14): `.commandsGroup('Management Commands:')` to organize visible command output\n- **Colored help** (v13): `styleTitle()` etc. via `.configureHelp()`\n- **Dual long flags** (v13.1): `--ws, --workspace` pattern if desired\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Extract shared bootstrap into `entrypoints/bootstrap/`\n\n```\nentrypoints/bootstrap/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ index.ts              # re-exports all layers\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ core.ts              # dotenv, credentials, api/init, telemetry, sentry, tracing, shutdown coord, error handlers, i18n\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ auth.ts              # certs, auth token, orgId provider, host identity, feature flags warm\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ settings.ts          # settingsService.initialize, autonomy defaults, built-in droids\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ platform.ts          # Windows update, stale binary cleanup, console encoding\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ sandbox.ts           # sandbox service init\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ tools.ts             # task tool manager init\nв””в”Җв”Җ runtime-settings.ts  # --settings arg extraction + resolution\n```\n\nEach layer is a standalone async function. Entrypoints compose them:\n\n```ts\n// entrypoints/search/run.ts (~20 lines)\nimport { bootstrapCore } from '../bootstrap/core';\nimport { bootstrapPlatform } from '../bootstrap/platform';\nimport { bootstrapAuth } from '../bootstrap/auth';\nimport { bootstrapSettings } from '../bootstrap/settings';\n\nawait bootstrapCore();\nawait bootstrapPlatform();\nawait bootstrapAuth();\nawait bootstrapSettings();\n\nconst { createSearchCommand } = await import('@/commands/search');\n// ... parse + run\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Per-entrypoint `command.ts` using `addCommand()` factory pattern\n\nEach CLI subcommand becomes a folder with two files:\n\n```\nentrypoints/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ bootstrap/           # shared layers\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ tui/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ command.ts       # factory: exports makeCommand() вҶ’ Command\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ run.ts           # heavy bootstrap (uses bootstrap/ layers)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ exec/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ command.ts\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ run.ts\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ daemon/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ command.ts\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ run.ts\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ search/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ command.ts\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ run.ts\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ update/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ command.ts\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ run.ts\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ mcp/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ command.ts\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ run.ts\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ plugin/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ command.ts\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ run.ts\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ computer/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ command.ts\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ run.ts\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ wiki-read/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ command.ts\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ run.ts\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ wiki-search/   ... (same pattern)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ wiki-upload/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ push-git-ai-notes/\nв””в”Җв”Җ git-ai-checkpoint-hook/\n```\n\n**`command.ts` pattern** вҖ” lightweight, only imports `commander` + constants:\n\n```ts\n// entrypoints/daemon/command.ts\nimport { Command, Option } from 'commander';\nimport { DAEMON_LISTEN_MODE_VALUES } from '@/commands/daemon/constants';\nimport { DaemonListenMode } from '@/commands/daemon/enums';\n\nexport function makeCommand(): Command {\n  return new Command('daemon')\n    .description('Run the Factory daemon server')\n    .addOption(new Option('-p, --port <number>', 'TCP port to listen on'))\n    .addOption(new Option('--host <address>', 'Host address to bind to'))\n    .addOption(new Option('--unix <path>', 'Unix socket path'))\n    .addOption(new Option('-d, --debug', 'Enable debug logging'))\n    .addOption(\n      new Option('--listen <transport>', 'Daemon transport')\n        .choices(DAEMON_LISTEN_MODE_VALUES)\n        .default(DaemonListenMode.WebSocket)\n    )\n    .addOption(new Option('--enable-child-ipc', 'Enable IPC'))\n    .addOption(new Option('--droid-path <path>', 'Path to droid executable'))\n    .addOption(new Option('--liveness-fd <fd>', 'Monitor parent via pipe'))\n    .addOption(new Option('--parent-pid <pid>', 'Monitor parent process'))\n    .addOption(new Option('--remote-access', 'Allow remote access'))\n    .allowUnknownOption(true)\n    .helpOption(false)\n    .action(async () => { await import('./run.js'); });\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Rewrite `index.ts` as thin declarative dispatcher\n\n```ts\nimport { Command, Option } from 'commander';\n\n// Lightweight factory imports (no heavy deps вҖ” only commander + constants)\nimport { makeCommand as makeDaemonCmd } from '@/entrypoints/daemon/command';\nimport { makeCommand as makeSearchCmd } from '@/entrypoints/search/command';\nimport { makeCommand as makeUpdateCmd } from '@/entrypoints/update/command';\nimport { makeCommand as makeMcpCmd } from '@/entrypoints/mcp/command';\nimport { makeCommand as makePluginCmd } from '@/entrypoints/plugin/command';\nimport { makeCommand as makeComputerCmd } from '@/entrypoints/computer/command';\nimport { makeCommand as makeExecCmd } from '@/entrypoints/exec/command';\n// ... hidden commands\n\nconst program = new Command();\nprogram\n  .name('droid')\n  .description(\"Droid - Factory's AI coding agent in your terminal\")\n  .version(process.env.CLI_VERSION || 'unknown', '-v, --version')\n  .enablePositionalOptions()\n  // Global TUI options (needed for correct argv routing)\n  .addOption(new Option('--settings <path>', 'Runtime settings file'))\n  .addOption(new Option('-r, --resume [sessionId]', 'Resume a session'))\n  .addOption(new Option('--fork <sessionId>', 'Fork and resume'))\n  .addOption(new Option('--cwd <path>', 'Working directory'))\n  .addOption(new Option('-w, --worktree [name]', 'Run in git worktree'))\n  .addOption(new Option('--worktree-dir <path>', 'Worktree directory'))\n  .addOption(new Option('--append-system-prompt <text>', 'Append to system prompt'))\n  .addOption(new Option('--append-system-prompt-file <path>', 'Append file to system prompt'))\n  .helpOption('-h, --help');\n\n// Visible commands (use v14 help groups)\nprogram\n  .addCommand(makeDaemonCmd())\n  .addCommand(makeSearchCmd())\n  .addCommand(makeUpdateCmd())\n  .addCommand(makeMcpCmd())\n  .addCommand(makePluginCmd())\n  .addCommand(makeComputerCmd());\n\n// Hidden commands\nprogram.addCommand(makeExecCmd());\n// ... wiki-read, wiki-search, etc.\n\n// Default: TUI (allowExcessArguments for free-form prompt)\nprogram\n  .allowUnknownOption(true)\n  .allowExcessArguments(true)\n  .arguments('[prompt...]')\n  .action(async () => { await import('@/entrypoints/tui/run.js'); });\n\nprogram.exitOverride();\nawait program.parseAsync(process.argv);\n```\n\nDelete old `entrypoints/subcommands.ts` once all commands have their own entrypoint.\n\n---\n\n## `commands/` folder вҖ” untouched\n\nAll existing `commands/*.ts` files stay in place. The entrypoint `run.ts` files import from them (`createSearchCommand()`, `createDaemonCommand()`, etc.).\n\n---\n\n## Execution order\n\n1. **Upgrade commander** to `^14.0.3`, fix breaking changes (allowExcessArguments, etc.)\n2. **Phase 1** вҖ” create `entrypoints/bootstrap/` shared layers\n3. **Phase 2** вҖ” create per-command `command.ts` + `run.ts` folders\n4. **Phase 3** вҖ” rewrite `index.ts` using `addCommand()` pattern, delete `subcommands.ts`\n\nEach step is independently shippable as a PR.",
