igs with Siggy for factory-mono. Use when auditing rollout state, validating live Statsig values, or making approved Statsig changes.\naws-sso-user-provisioner: Add users to AWS SSO with a specified role. Use when asked to grant AWS SSO access, add someone to AWS, or give AWS permissions to a team member.\norg-migration: Write, test, and run Firestore organization document migrations using the apps/scripts migration framework. Use when backfilling fields on org docs, migrating data between collections, or running bulk updates across all organizations.\nclean-feature-flags: Audit and retire entries in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` against live Statsig state. Use when sweeping launched/abandoned flags, draining the registry, or producing a per-flag cleanup PR with surgical, hermetic commits.\nautomated-qa-prod: Automated QA testing for the Factory web app PROD/PREPROD environments. Use when you want to run a smoke test of the preprod or production environment. For dev environment QA, use the automated-qa-dev skill instead.\nplaywright-e2e-mcp: Create Playwright e2e tests for apps/web using Chrome DevTools MCP.\nqa-web: QA tests for the Factory web app. Covers login, signup, onboarding, session creation, settings, billing, and navigation flows. Invoked by the qa orchestrator when web-related files change.\nqa-backend: QA tests for the Factory backend API. Covers API endpoint validation, health checks, authentication flows, and API response verification. Invoked by the qa orchestrator when backend files change.\nqa-cli: QA tests for the Factory CLI (Droid). Covers CLI startup, slash commands, interactive TUI, session management, and command execution. Invoked by the qa orchestrator when CLI-related files change.\nqa: Run QA tests for Factory. Analyzes git diff to determine affected areas, runs configured test flows with multiple personas, and generates diff-targeted tests. Use when testing PRs, releases, or smoke testing environments.\nautomated-qa-dev: Automated QA testing for the Factory web app DEV environment only. Use when you want to run a full E2E smoke test of the dev environment. For production/preprod QA, use the automated-qa-prod skill instead.\nlocal-web-debug: Reproduce and debug web app bugs on the local dev environment. Use when a user reports a bug and you need to reproduce it locally, inspect logs, identify root cause, and optionally apply a fix.\ncli-e2e-testing: Writes end-to-end tests for Factory CLI using @factory/tui-test. Use when writing e2e tests, debugging test failures, or testing terminal interactions.\ncli-resource-analysis: Diagnose CLI runtime performance -- CPU hotspots, memory/RSS, render latency, benchmark regressions. Use when TUI is slow, RSS is high, a benchmark regresses, refreshing PR profiling evidence, or validating a performance fix.\nbigquery-platform-analytics: Query Factory's BigQuery platform analytics dataset (`factory-production.analytics`) for org usage, tokens, billing, sessions, users, trials, OTEL telemetry, and platform metrics. Use when investigating customer usage, billing questions, session analytics, user activity, trial conversions, or platform KPIs. Do NOT use for eval/benchmark data -- see `evals-investigation` for eval runs, harbor trials, saas-bench results, and GKE eval dataplane logs.\nmemory-leak-analysis: Analyze V8 heap snapshots to identify memory leaks in Factory CLI. Use when investigating high memory usage, analyzing .heapsnapshot files, or debugging memory issues.\nsentry-debug: Deep-dive debugging of a Sentry issue by cross-referencing with Axiom logs and Firestore entity state. Use when a user shares a Sentry URL and needs full-stack root cause analysis.\naxiom-dashboard-ops: Audit, revamp, and operate Axiom dashboards in the factory-ai-hgct org. Use when asked to fix, restructure, or extend an Axiom dashboard (Continuous Learning, LLM Traffic, Assembly API, Daemon, etc.), debug a chart rendering as a table instead of a time series, repoint dataset references after a telemetry migration, or wire env/org SmartFilters across panels. Sibling skills `continuous-learning-dashboard` and `llm-traffic-dashboard` cover dashboard-specific quirks; everything general lives here.\ndaily-platform-metrics: Fetch daily platform health metrics from Axiom, Sentry, and GitHub Actions. Use when running the daily metrics check or investigating platform reliability.\ndaily-cli-bug-report: Analyze recent CLI bug reports from Axiom and S3. Use when asked to analyze CLI bug reports, investigate CLI errors, or create a bug report summary.\naxiom: Query Axiom datasets for CLI/TUI logs and metrics, frontend logs and metrics, server metrics, and API logs. Use when investigating CLI errors, user issues, platform-specific problems, analyzing CLI usage patterns, or debugging frontend issues.\noncall-alert-triage: Investigate and triage oncall Axiom/Sentry alerts. Use when the user provides alert data for their oncall week and needs help investigating root causes, classifying severity, and documenting findings.\nworkos-lookup-user: Look up a WorkOS user by email address. Use when asked to find a user ID, look up a user, or resolve an email to a WorkOS user. Supports both dev and prod environments.\nfirestore-debug: Query and inspect Firestore data in dev or prod for debugging. Use when investigating user data, session state, org config, or any Firestore document lookup.\nevals-investigation: Investigate Factory eval runs using BigQuery (`factory-production.factory_evals`) and persisted GKE dataplane logs. Use when analyzing eval/benchmark results, comparing models on terminal-bench v1/v2 or factory-legacy-bench, investigating trial failures, inspecting Harbor runner logs, computing pass rates, or aggregating tokens/cost across trials.\ncontinuous-learning-dashboard: Operate the Axiom \"Continuous Learning\" dashboard. Use when asked to add/modify panels for skills, custom droids, or Signal Health; debug stale data; or update the skill/droid categorization. For general Axiom dashboard operations, see sibling skill `axiom-dashboard-ops`.\nllm-traffic-dashboard: Operate the Axiom \"LLM Traffic\" dashboard. Use when asked to add/modify panels for LLM provider traffic, error categorization, model-family breakdowns, or 429 attribution. For general Axiom dashboard operations, see sibling skill `axiom-dashboard-ops`.\nhttp-toolkit-intercept: Intercept and debug Droid CLI HTTP traffic using HTTP Toolkit. Use when you need to inspect LLM API calls, Factory API requests, auth flows, or debug network-level issues in the Droid CLI.\nsentry-error-cleanup: Evaluate a batch of Sentry errors from a production alert view, classify each into a remediation strategy (code fix, manual resolve, or escalate), and either implement fixes or produce a triage report.\ne2b-remote-debugging: Pull and analyze droid logs from E2B sandboxes, and push code changes to sandboxes for debugging.\nmodel-partner-feedback: Analyze benchmark evaluation runs for a model and produce a polished feedback document for an external model provider team. Use when preparing behavioral feedback for NVIDIA, MiniMax, DeepSeek, or other model partners based on Terminal Bench results.\ndebug-overview: Route debugging requests to the appropriate sub-skill(s). Use as the default entry point for any debugging task.\nreproduce-llm-errors: Reproduce production LLM errors locally. Use when you need to confirm a bug exists before fixing, verify a fix resolves it, or create a regression test for an LLM proxy/converter error.\nclean-model-registry: Clean up the LLM model registry by removing feature flags from fully-launched models and deleting deprecated/EAP models. Use when asked to clean up models, remove feature flags from launched models, or remove deprecated EAP preview models.\nadd-llm-model: Add a new LLM model to the codebase. Use when integrating new models from Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, or other providers, including EAP/preview models with secret