          "text": "<system-reminder>\n\nUser system info (darwin 25.4.0)\n\nModel: Claude Opus 4.7\nToday's date: 2026-05-22\nUser language: en\n\n# The commands below were executed at the start of all sessions to gather context about the environment.\n# You do not need to repeat them, unless you think the environment has changed.\n# Remember: They are not necessarily related to the current conversation, but may be useful for context.\n\n% pwd\n/Users/david/Desktop/dev/factory/factory-mono-delta\n\n% ls\nAGENTS.md\napps\ndocs\nevals\nfirebase.json\nfirestore.indexes.json\nfirestore.rules\ninfra\ninternal\nknip.json\nnode_modules\npackage-lock.json\npackage.json\npackages\nqa-evidence\nREADME.md\nstorage.rules\ntsconfig.json\ntsconfig.next.json\nturbo.json\n\n% git status -b --porcelain | head -n1\ndgu/bootstrap-effect\n\n% git status --porcelain\n M apps/cli/package.json\n D apps/cli/src/entrypoints/bootstrap/auth.ts\n M apps/cli/src/entrypoints/bootstrap/lightweight.ts\n D apps/cli/src/entrypoints/bootstrap/platform.ts\n M package-lock.json\n M packages/logging/src/metadata/types.ts\n M packages/logging/src/metrics/enums.ts\n M packages/logging/src/metrics/types.ts\n?? apps/cli/prompt.txt\n?? apps/cli/scripts/decrypt-mcp-oauth.mjs\n?? apps/cli/src/commands/.#parseTagFlag.ts\n?? apps/cli/src/entrypoints/bootstrap/effect/\n\n% git log --oneline -5\ne6798a7a71 feat(droid-core): add native Bedrock Converse BYOK support (#13787)\n5331fecc8b feat(services, utils): load system-managed settings from platform paths (#13857)\n7414e6ae0c feat(evals): add support for arbitrary `droid exec` flags (#13883)\nf26c5adb87 feat(frontend, desktop, common): audio cues for completion + awaiting-input sessions (#13898)\n94e44c6ba7 feat(monorepo): propagate selected organization header (#13767)\n\n% git symbolic-ref refs/remotes/origin/HEAD\nrefs/remotes/origin/dev\n\n# Codebase and user instructions are shown below. Instructions from files closest to your current directory take precedence over those further up the hierarchy.\n## Project Instructions:\n% cat /Users/david/Desktop/dev/factory/factory-mono-delta/AGENTS.md\n<coding_guidelines>\n# Agents Guidelines for Factory Monorepo\n\n## Critical Requirements\n\n- **packages/frontend work**: Follow [`docs/ui-development.md`](./docs/ui-development.md) - always use `@factory/core-ui` components\n- **API endpoints**: Define types in `@factory/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` - see [`docs/examples/api-type-conventions.md`](./docs/examples/api-type-conventions.md)\n\n---\n\n## Reference Docs (check when relevant)\n\n- [`/docs/examples/`](./docs/examples/) - End-to-end implementation patterns\n- [`/memories/`](./memories/) - Session context and notes from previous work\n- [`docs/frontend.md`](./docs/frontend.md) - Frontend architecture\n- [`docs/feature-flags.md`](./docs/feature-flags.md) - Statsig feature flags\n- [`docs/error-handling.md`](./docs/error-handling.md) - Error patterns\n- [`docs/unit-tests.md`](./docs/unit-tests.md) - Testing conventions\n- [`docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md`](./docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md) - Playwright E2E testing for apps/web\n- [`docs/pre-pr-checklist.md`](./docs/pre-pr-checklist.md) - PR quality checklist (read before creating PRs)\n- [`docs/services-environment.md`](./docs/services-environment.md) - How env vars flow into service DI configs (read before adding env vars to a service)\n\n---\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix        # Lint + format (preferred over npm run lint)\nnpm run test       # Run all tests\nnpm run typecheck  # TypeScript checking\nnpm run knip       # Detect unused exports\nnpm run build      # Build all packages\nnpm run dev:web    # Start backend, web, storybook, admin, daemon (works over SSH)\nnpm run dev:desktop # Start backend, web, storybook, admin, desktop (local only)\nnpm run clean      # Clear all caches\n```\n\n**Do NOT use `npm run dev`** at the root вҖ” it is intentionally disabled. Use `dev:web` or `dev:desktop` above.\n\nFor CLI dev, run `droid-dev` (hosted) or `droid-local` (local API) separately after `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`.\n\n**Dev server logs:** When running `dev:web` or `dev:desktop`, each app streams its output to both console and a log file on disk. You can inspect logs at any time:\n\n| App     | Log file                       |\n| ------- | ------------------------------ |\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin   | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log`   |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon  | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log`  |\n\nUse `tail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` to live-stream, or `cat` / `grep` the file to search for errors.\n\n**Filtering to specific packages (IMPORTANT):** You **must** use `--` before `--filter`, otherwise npm eats the flag and turbo runs ALL packages. A full unfiltered `npm run test` consumes ~9 GB of RAM.\n\n```bash\n# CORRECT - filter is passed through to turbo:\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n\n# WRONG - npm eats --filter, turbo runs everything:\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n```\n\nThis applies to all turbo-based scripts: `test`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `fix`, `build`.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\nSee [`docs/repo-overview.md`](./docs/repo-overview.md) for the full apps/packages catalog.\n\n**Key apps:**\n\n- `apps/web` - Main web application (Vite + React)\n- `apps/desktop` - Electron desktop app\n- `apps/cli` (daemon mode) - Background daemon service (`droid daemon`)\n- `apps/cli` - Droid CLI\n- `apps/backend` - Backend API only (web UI deprecated)\n\n**Key packages:**\n\n- `@factory/core-ui` - Design system (mandatory for UI)\n- `@factory/common` - Shared types, enums, API contracts\n- `@factory/frontend` - Shared frontend features\n- `@factory/droid-core` - AI agent core library\n\n### Client <-> daemon protocol\n\n- Shared JSON-RPC envelope/base protocol schemas live in `packages/common/src/shared/schemas.ts`\n- Daemon-side protocol schemas and exported types live under `packages/common/src/daemon/`\n- Client-side protocol schemas and exported types live under `packages/common/src/droid/`\n- `FACTORY_PROTOCOL_VERSION` lives in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/constants.ts`\n- Protocol manifest CI enforcement lives in `apps/scripts/src/protocol-manifest/`; see `apps/scripts/src/protocol-manifest/README.md` before changing protocol schemas or protocol versioning rules\n\n---\n\n## Code Conventions\n\n- New API endpoints need types in `@factory/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`\n- New UI components must use `@factory/core-ui` primitives (no raw `<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>`)\n- No hardcoded colors (use `colors.semantics`)\n- Extend existing abstractions rather than adding workaround logic in callers\n- Extract shared utilities instead of duplicating transformations across files\n- Don't remove safeguards (`.strict()`, assertions, validation) without documenting why\n- Search for existing patterns before creating new ones: `rg \"keyword\" --type ts`\n- Do not log user-generated content (session titles, message content, file contents, tool call params/results) in telemetry вҖ” CMEK-encrypted orgs expect this data to be opaque to the platform. See `packages/logging/src/metadata/types.ts` for the full policy.\n\n---\n\n## Testing\n\n- Do **not** run `npm run test`, `npm run typecheck`, or `npm run fix` unless explicitly requested\n- Prefer targeted checks where possible and ask before running repo-wide validators\n- For CLI unit tests, prefer `npm run test` / filtered `npm run test -- --filter=@factory/cli`. If you bypass npm scripts and invoke the runner directly, use `npx vitest`; CLI test helpers run under Vitest.\n- For `infra/` validation, use OpenTofu (`tofu init` / `tofu validate` / `tofu fmt`) instead of Terraform\n- See each app's README.md for app-specific testing details and conventions\n\n---\n\n## Debugging\n\nSee [`docs/debugging-daemon.md`](./docs/debugging-daemon.md) for the full guide.\n\n**Quick checklist:**\n\n- Rebuilt CLI after changes (`cd apps/cli && npm run setup`)\n- Restarted daemon process\n- Started new session (not reusing old one)\n- Checking correct log directory (`~/.factory-dev/` for dev)\n\n---\n\n## PR Conventions\n\nFollow the template in `.github/pull_request_template.md` and review [`docs/pre-pr-checklist.md`](./docs/pre-pr-checklist.md) before submitting.\n\n- **Title**: Conventional Commits format - `type(scope): description`\n  - Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\n  - Scope: workspace name from `apps/*` or `packages/*`, or `monorepo`\n- **Description**: Must include Linear ticket (e.g., `Closes FAC-1234`)\n</coding_guidelines>\n\n\n\nIMPORTANT:\n- Double check the tools installed in the environment before using them.\n- Never call a file editing tool for the same file in parallel.\n- Always prefer the Grep, Glob and LS tools over shell commands like find, grep, or ls for codebase exploration.\n- Always prefer using the absolute paths when using tools, to avoid any ambiguity.\n- To enter a mission, the user needs to run the `/missions` slash command.\n\n</system-reminder>",
